  "articleSummary": "This article, aimed at JavaScript developers, explains two common pitfalls with Promises: they cannot be used like synchronous values (requiring `.then()` to access results), and they silently accept `null` or `undefined` as arguments to `.then()` and `.catch()`, which can cause unexpected behavior. The tutorial uses code examples to illustrate how passing `console.log()` (which returns `undefined`) instead of `console.log` (a function) leads to silent failures. The core thesis is that Promises have subtle, non-obvious behaviors that can introduce bugs if developers are not aware of these \"gotchas.\"",
